I. To introduce a form of DoS protection:

iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --syn --dport 110 -m connlimit --connlimit-above 2 -j REJECT
iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --syn --dport 995 -m connlimit --connlimit-above 2 -j REJECT

II. Create a stunnel config to provide a pop3-ssl service:

************
pid =
setgid = stunnel
setuid = stunnel
service = ooop

[pop3s]
cert = /usr/local/etc/stun.pem
accept  = 995
connect = localhost:110
TIMEOUTbusy = 30
TIMEOUTclose = 0
TIMEOUTconnect = 5
************

III. New directives in ooop.conf:

rbl_condemns_the_message=1
surbl_condemns_the_message=1

